  <scopecontent id="4473198411ec1d049e4191147627de7a">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>Collection contains files pertaining to the preparation, production, and promotion of the South Africa UPDATE Series. The Ford Foundation initiated the UPDATE Series project in order to update the South Africa: Time Running Out report (SATRO) that was published in 1981 by the Study Commission on U.S. Policy Towards Southern Africa. The series consists of five monographs. Each book focuses on a particular theme regarding political developments in South Africa during the 1980s. Subjects covered in the series include international relations between South Africa and the United States, politics in the region of Southern Africa, political activism of black South Africans, reforms made to the Apartheid system, and the state of civil rights in South Africa.</p><p>
The bulk of the collection is contained within the chronological files in the first series. These files consist of correspondence, memos, drafts, invoices, purchase orders, expense reports, budget information, petty cash vouchers, agreements, and consultant requests. They document the work of the UPDATE Series Editor John de St. Jorre, Associate Editor Elinor Bowles, and Editorial Board in reaching out to prospective authors and readers of monographs, revising manuscripts, preparing the books' design, publishing and disseminating the books, and promoting the series. </p><p>
The last two series in the collection are chiefly comprised of the UPDATE Series editors' correspondence with monograph authors, research assistants, and monograph testimonial writers. Copies of monograph testimonials are also included in the third series.</p><p>
Material in the collection originated from a select group of boxes that contained Ford Foundation program strategy records. The documents' original storage containers and content indicated that they all concerned the South Africa UPDATE Series, and the records were therefore processed as a discrete collection.</p>  </scopecontent>
